!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

dairy /ˈdɛərɪ/

(dairies) 

1. N-COUNT A dairy is a company that sells milk and food made from milk, such as butter, cream, and cheese. 乳品公司 

例： In my childhood, local dairies bought milk from local farmers. 在我小时候，本地的乳品公司向当地农场主收购牛奶。 

2. ADJ Dairy is used to refer to foods such as butter and cheese that are made from milk. 奶制的 [ADJ n] 

例： He avoids all meat and dairy products. 他不吃任何肉类和奶制品。 

3. ADJ Dairy is used to refer to the use of cattle to produce milk rather than meat. 产乳的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...a small vegetable and dairy farm. …一个种菜、养奶牛的小农场。

</div>

